							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I just got my level 27 spell : Bria's Thrilling Balad (apprentice I).
<br />
And of course I tested its effect in combat because that's the only place where it really matters.
<br />

<br />
Without any power regen song: 9 power per tick
<br />
With Bria's Stirring Balad (adept I): add 4 power per tick
<br />
With Cassindra's Chant of Clarity: add 6 power per tick
<br />
With Bria's Thrilling Balad (apprentice I): add 7 power per tick
<br />

<br />
When I say they don't stack, I mean that their effects wont add, not that you cant play the songs at the same time.
<br />

<br />
So I have to agree with Neofelis that as soon as you get Bria's Thrilling Balad both other songs become useless.
<br />

<br />
Aegolin, 27 Troubador</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
