							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This was very common in EQ1 as well.  Bard basic haste song and enchanter or shaman haste buffs, for example.  Both icons would show up, but the effects did not add together (they did not "stack.").  Also, there is the issue of multi-effect songs, that is, songs that raise several attributes at once.  Both icons will appear, but again where the two effects overlap, they may not add together.
<br />

<br />
When people talk about "stacking" they mean that the affects ADD TOGETHER.  It hellps when everyone uses the same definition for "stack" <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>angelgreen wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">This is the first I've heard of songs that show up as working, but actually only the one with the higher level is doing anything.  Are there others like this?  I've figured that as long as I got the icon, it was doing <span style="font-style: italic">something</span>.  Anyone know of a chart/list of other songs that seem to stack, but really don't?
<br />

<br />
I wonder if this happens across professions.  When I'm in a group, and non-bards are casting their buffs, maybe some are essentially cancelling out others.  If so, that would be nice to know too.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
