<br />

<br />
I have to go with the first definition. In any game I've played, 'stacking' of buffs meant that both would be castable at the same time AND that their effects accumulated (Hence the word stack - a pile of things one on top of the other). 
<br />

<br />
The case you describe is just a non-blocking - the fact that both buffs share a feature (agi) does not preclude them from working together, but you only get the benefit from ONE of them (the higher one).
<br />

<br />
When 2 different buffs that give the exact same benefit but differ in strength are castable on a char at the same time but only the higher works (or in some worst cases in certain games, the 2nd one cast overwrites the first regardless of it's relative benefit) that is not stacking, that's just wasting Conc (or power, mana, whatever s relevant to that game).<br />_________________<br />Paitaan, 20th season Troubadour
<br />
Antonya Bayle</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
