							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Fineus wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Stacking is non-blocking; the two are the same thing.  (thats the predominate way it was used in EQ1... but people would misuse it there as well.)</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Believe it or not, but there IS a whole world of MMORPG's out there, that are NOT EQ1.
<br />

<br />
I find this annoying obsession to relate, compare and judge every single feature of this game to that game very prevalent on EQ2 boards everywhere, despite repeated clarifications from Developers that THIS IS A DIFFERENT GAME.
<br />

<br />
I don't care how Bards were in EQ1, what spells they had or didn't have, nor do I care about enchanters, warriors or whatever. This is NOT an EQ2 expansion pack, this is a NEW game. The assumption (that some make) that everyone here has played EQ1, EQL, Champions of Norrath etc., etc. is as much unrealistic as it is small minded.
<br />

<br />
This is rant not directed you personally I must stress, just a pet peeve of mine I thought I'd air out.
<br />

<br />
But to the point in question here - in over 5 different MMORPG's I've played, not counting EQ1 which I played briefly and didn't like much, stacking meant 2 buffs giving cumulative effect. That's why it's called STACKING - the piling of one ON TOP of the other, not NEXT to it.
<br />

<br />
And it refers to any sort of buff/debuff given by any class. Class A's self-only mana regen could either stack or not with class B's mana regen group song, for example. 
<br />

<br />
Again, there's the question of what happens when buffs do not stack (would B's song overwrite A's self buff in any case, only if it were stronger, have no impact at all, etc.), but that usually differs on a case-by-case basis. The fact remains that this IS the world-wide, cross-game cross-genre definition of stacking.<br />_________________<br />Paitaan, 20th season Troubadour
<br />
Antonya Bayle</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
