						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First Generation MMOs had a language, but it was stupid and geeky and it di not really live on, except in a few words.
<br />

<br />
Second Generation MMOs, like UO, had the same downfall.
<br />

<br />
The Third Generation MMO, Everquest 1, was widely popular, enough to be mistaken by many as the First Generation.  It used some of the earlier language and created the modern MMO Language.
<br />

<br />
Fourth Generation MMOs, like AC and DAoC, were EQ Lite clones, and used the same language.
<br />

<br />
Fifth Generation MMOs like EQ2 and SWG continue to use the same language.
<br />

<br />
This continuity of language has bred the Accepted, Proper Language of MMOs to date back to the Third Generation, EQ1.  Thus, when talking language, EQ 1 Language is the pure or high version.  Any other version would be a local dialect.  Dialects are proper within their context, but are not the pure or high version.
<br />

<br />
The United Kingdom speaks the Language British English.  In the USA, we speak the Language American English.  Even though they are rooted in the same foundation, the two are clearly seperate, in much the way of the UO and the EQ languages.
<br />

<br />
The American English has dialects, like the Southern, Cajun, Bostonian, and Texan versions.  These are not the pure, they are just local versions... the same as DAoC, SWG, EQ2, AO, and AC.  Bostonians may believe they speak proper American English, but everyone knows y'all speak funny up there.
<br />

<br />
This is the reason why gamers constantly refer to items in EQ1 terms.  If you never played it, you might not know what you learned in one game is a dialect.  But everyone should be able to make the common EQ1 base language.  EQ1 was a complex game that required a language to describe it.  MMOs since have been simplifactions, and have not really needed much in the way of new terms.  The few new terms, mostly the handful created to describe the new game's HOOK feature, were incorperated in EQ1, as SOE stole the ideas and used them.
<br />

<br />
Thus, MMO is a live and changing language.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Sonsi Carns
<br />
3X  Human Dirge of Qeynos
<br />
Dawn of Evolution
<br />
Befallen</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
					</table></td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td class="row1" width="150" align="left" valign="middle"><span class="gensmall">&nbsp;<a href="#top" class="gensmall">Back to top&nbsp;&raquo;</a></span></td>
					<td class="row1" width="100%" height="28" valign="bottom" nowrap="nowrap">

						<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" height="18" width="18">
